  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Swift-DocC Plugin"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Generating Documentation for Extended Types"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "By default, the Swift-DocC plugin ignores extensions you make to types that are not from the module you’re generating documentation for.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To include documentation for extended types, add the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--include-extended-types",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag to your invocations:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swift package generate-documentation --include-extended-types"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Extension support is available when using Swift 5.8 or later and the Swift-DocC plugin 1.2 or later.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Understanding-What-is-Included-by-Default",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Understanding What is Included by Default",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Not everything that is declared in an extension is hidden behind the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--include-extended-types",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag. If the extension is declared in the same target as the type it is extending, the extension’s contents will be included in the documentation by default.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "public struct Sloth { }",
            "",
            "extension Sloth {",
            "    \/\/ This function is included in the",
            "    \/\/ documentation by default.",
            "    public func wake() { \/* ... *\/ }",
            "}",
            "",
            "\/\/ `Collection` is from the standard library,",
            "\/\/ not the `SlothCreator` library, so this is",
            "\/\/ what we call an \"extended type\".",
            "extension Collection where Element == Sloth {",
            "    \/\/ This property is not included in",
            "    \/\/ the documentation by default.",
            "    public func wake() {",
            "        for sloth in self {",
            "            sloth.wake()",
            "        }",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Finding-Extended-Types-in-your-Documentation",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Finding Extended Types in your Documentation",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Extended Types are part of the documentation archive of the target that declares the extensions.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "identifier" : "extended-type-example",
              "type" : "image"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Within that documentation archive, Extended Types are grouped by the Extended Module they belong to. You can find the latter on your documentation’s landing page in a section called “Extended Modules”. In our example from above, we have one Extended Module called “Swift” - the name of the standard library. This page can be referenced like this: ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "``SlothCreator\/Swift``",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The Extended Type ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "``SlothCreator\/Swift\/Collection``",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is a child of the Extended Module and is listed under “Extended Protocols” on the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "``SlothCreator\/Swift``",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " page.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "The references above use the full path, including the name of the catalog’s target, ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "SlothCreator",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : ". This should help to understand the symbol’s exact location, but usually isn’t necessary.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
